The paper discusses security threats in wireless sensor networks, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The focus of the paper is on detecting sleep deprivation attacks, which is a type of attack on the network infrastructure (cs.NI). The proposed framework is based on distributed collaborative mechanism, which involves coordination and communication among multiple nodes, making it a system-level approach (cs.SY). The paper also mentions the use of anomaly detection technique, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data science (cs.DS).
